    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter April 9th with a lean but efficient lineup, headlined by the leadoff placement of **Colt Keith**. With a score of 66.33, **Colt Keith** stands as our most reliable asset today; he benefits significantly from hitting at the top of the order and facing Abel, whose 4.28 xERA suggests a prime opportunity for multi-hit potential. We are also deploying **Chase Meidroth** in the assumed leadoff spot against Seth Lugo. While **Chase Meidroth** faces a right-on-right disadvantage, his 62.08 score remains robust, bolstered by an favorable wind forecast and the statistical upside of hitting at the top of the lineup.\n\nConversely, we are exercising caution with **Carson Benge** (42.63). Despite the marginal score, **Carson Benge** is only being started due to depth requirements; the left-on-left matchup against Eduardo Rodriguez creates a clear platoon penalty that significantly caps his ceiling. The most difficult decision today involved managing our bench, where stars like **Yordan Alvarez**, **Junior Caminero**, **Pete Crow-Armstrong**, and **Trea Turner** are unavailable due to team off-days. Had they been active, the optimizer would have immediately moved **Carson Benge** to the pine to clear space for the elite stolen base profiles of **Pete Crow-Armstrong** or **Trea Turner**. We continue to monitor the status of **Victor Scott II**, **Caleb Durbin**, **Hyeseong Kim**, **Kazuma Okamoto**, **Zac Veen**, **Lars Nootbaar**, **Logan O'Hoppe**, **Josh Smith**, **Dillon Dingler**, **Jerar Encarnacion**, **Luis Pena**, **Kyle Schwarber**, and **Christian Yelich** as we look to optimize our SB-heavy strategy in upcoming rotations.",
